headline: How Does CrowdStrike Stack Up After Announcing a $1.3B Buyback Program?
summary: If you are trying to decide what to do with your CrowdStrike Holdings shares, you are not alone. It is easy to see why, with the stock trailing off about 10% in the past month and giving up some of its momentum from earlier this year. Even so, longer-term investors have reasons to smile: the stock is up 21% year-to-date and over 54% when you look back at the past twelve months.
